luminosities higher than\n$\\sim14000\\,{\\mathrm{L}}_\\odot$, and consequently at pulsation periods longer\nthan $\\sim800$ days. The final grain radii range from 0.25 micron to 0.6\nmicron. The amount of condensed Si is typically between 10% and 40%, with\ngas-to-dust mass ratios between 500 and 4000.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Apr 2019 17:35:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 May 2019 13:14:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-10"}
